A tag is a label you put on an important commit.

Tags are often used for versions like:
  
  v1.0
  
  v2.0
  
  v3.0

We use tags to mark important points in a project.

  “This commit is Version 1.0 of my project.”


Create a simple tag

  git tag v1.0

Create a better tag with a message

  git tag -a v1.0 -m "Version 1.0 release"

To see all of the tags is:

  git tag
